  "title": "Health Attendant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u>Clinical Care</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Make frequent rounds and attend to residents’ needs. Ensure the safety, comfort and well-being of the residents and report residents’ needs to the nurse</li>\n  <li>Assist in ensuring the comfort and good personal hygiene of the residents under his/ her care, and keeping them clean, e.g. oral toilet, showering and grooming, trimming of nails, changing of diapers, changing of clothes and bed sheets</li>\n  <li>Assist in serving meals and oral feeding of resident without swallowing disorders</li>\n  <li>Assist nursing care staff in the transfer and positioning of non-ambulant residents</li>\n  <li>Assist and participate in residents’ recreational, occupational, social and therapy programmes</li>\n  <li>Assist nurses to ensure residents take their medicines</li>\n  <li>Accompany residents to specialist outpatient clinic for follow-up appointments and outing trips</li>\n  <li>Assist in last offices</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u>Quality</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Maintain a safe and clean environment, e.g. cleaning and mopping of spillage or discharges, cleaning of residents’ bed and bedside locker, making of beds</li>\n  <li>Participate in staff development programmes</li>\n  <li>Is responsible to be familiar with the Standard Operating Procedures (SOP) and all emergency protocols</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u>Administration</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Maintain accurate documentation of care rendered and confidentiality of residents’ information</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Primary/ Secondary education</li>\n</ul>",
